# Monorepo Stability

Nova Support is a pnpm + Turborepo monorepo (`apps/*`, `packages/*`). Prefer small, reversible changes.

## Scope

- Change only what the task requires. No drive-by refactors or unrelated files.
- Match existing naming, imports (`@/` in apps, `@nova/*` workspaces), and patterns in neighboring code.
- Do not invent parallel systems when a module already exists (billing, analytics, escalation, Shopify).

## Packages

| Package | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `@nova/api` | Fastify API, Prisma, Redis, Shopify, AI orchestration |
| `@nova/dashboard` | Next.js 14 embedded Shopify Admin app (`src/app`) |
| `@nova/gateway` | Edge gateway |
| `@nova/shared` | Shared Zod schemas and types (build before API consumers) |
| `@nova/ai` | Agent graph, LLM, RAG |
| `@nova/ui` | Shared UI + embeddable widget |

- Import via workspace packages (`@nova/shared`, `@nova/ai`), not deep relative paths across apps.
- After changing `packages/shared` or `packages/ai` public exports, run that package’s `build` (or `pnpm --filter @nova/shared build`) before typechecking dependents.
- After Prisma schema changes: `pnpm --filter @nova/api db:generate` (and add a migration under `apps/api/prisma/migrations/`).

## Secrets

- Never commit `.env` or real credentials. Update `.env.example` only with placeholder keys.
- Shopify access tokens stay encrypted at rest (`encryptPII` / `decryptPII`).

## Local ports

- Dashboard `3000`, API `3001`. Do not silently rebind without updating README and env examples.
